Utility parameters

Source: R/data.R
params_utility.Rd

Utility estimates by health state and disutilities by adverse event.

params_utility

Format

A list containing the following elements:

  • state_utility Utility estimates by health state.

  • as_disutility Disutility by health state.

State utility

The state_utility element is a data table with the following columns:

state_name

Name of the health state.

mean

Mean utility.

se

Standard error of utility.

ref

BibTeX reference for estimate.

Adverse event disutilities

The as_disutility element is a data table with the following columns:

ae_name

Name of the adverse event.

ae_abb

Abbreviation for the adverse event.

mean

Mean disutility.

se

Standard error of disutility.

ref

BibTeX reference for estimate.

Examples

print(params_utility)
#> $state_utility
#>    state_name   mean         se              ref
#> 1:         S1 0.7540 0.00000000 nafees2017health
#> 2:      P1/S2 0.6532 0.02223000 nafees2008health
#> 3:         P2 0.4734 0.03105848 nafees2008health
#>
